\paragraph{Context}
The context discusses the stability properties of general linear methods, introducing the stability matrix \(M(z)\) and its characteristic polynomial \(\Phi(w, z)\). The goal is to design methods whose stability resembles that of Runge-Kutta methods.

Variables:
\begin{itemize}
    \item \(M(z)\): stability matrix for a general linear method, \(M(z) = V + zB(I - zA)^{-1} U\)
    \item \(\Phi(w, z)\): characteristic polynomial of \(M(z)\), \(\Phi(w, z) = \det(wI - M(z))\)
    \item \(R(z)\): stability function (a rational function)
\end{itemize}

